A truck which picked up a crowd of children  celebrating the Moslem feast of Al-Adha plunged into a canal on Saturday,  drowning 17 of them and injuring six, Egyptian police said.
The accident happened on the road from Giza to Beni Seweif south of Cairo  when a tyre blew and the driver lost control.
Police said a head-on crash between a truck and car on another road near  Giza killed six people and injured five.
